data.chText: 她在一个男性居多的环境里工作。
data.enText: She works in a predominantly male environment.

tr: much greater in number or influence

value.def: You use predominantly to indicate which feature or quality is most noticeable in a situation.

example.ex: The landscape has remained predominantly rural in appearance.
example.tran: 这里的风景看上去还是以田园风光为主。

example.ex: Although it is predominantly a teenage problem, acne can occur in early childhood...
example.tran: 虽然粉刺多发于青少年时期，但也可能在刚进入童年时期就出现。

example.ex: His audience consists predominantly of groups of rugby-club revellers.
example.tran: 他的观众主要是橄榄球俱乐部里那些纵酒作乐的人。

gramarinfo.label: usu ADV group, also ADV after v

value.tran: 最显著地；占主导地位地
